msgid "Interviews - performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:6
msgid "Being present, alive and active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:8
msgid ""
"One of the most important things to manage in an interview is your own "
"posture and role in it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:10
msgid ""
"Far too many candidates expect it to be something like an examination at "
"school: they ask you the questions and you will do well to the extent "
"that you come up with the right answers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:12
msgid ""
"Some of it *is* similar. You will be asked questions. If you prepare "
"well, you'll do better. There are definitely many right and wrong "
"answers. If you are asked a question to test some required knowledge or "
"insight, you either have it or you don't."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:14
msgid ""
"But in most interviews, most of it is about discovering who you are, or "
"rather, who you will be if you get the job. *Doing well in the interview "
"means showing that you are a person who will do well in the role.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:16
msgid ""
"**A job interview is a business meeting.** Prepare for one. You are not "
"being inspected or examined, as if you were some merchandise. You are "
"coming to the table as a potential partner, a colleague, a team-mate, "
"because they have needs and you have skills and abilities that could meet"
" those needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:20
msgid "Applicant vs supplicant"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:24
msgid "Indeed there is an imbalance of power."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:26
msgid ""
"They are bigger than you, they have more money, there are more of them, "
"and of course, you applied to work with them, not the other way round. "
"It's too easy for candidates to adopt a passive posture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:28
msgid ""
"Remember, you are an *applicant*, not a *supplicant*. They may have set "
"the agenda, but they don't totally own it. You have an active role to "
"play. You need to be fully present in the encounter. You will be amazed "
"how much an interviewee who takes an active role in an interview can "
"influence its course."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:34
msgid "Needs, value, demonstration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:36
msgid ""
"In an interview, you must **demonstrate** how you can bring **value** "
"that meets their **needs**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:38
msgid "So, three questions for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:40
msgid ""
"**What do you think they need?** The nice thing about their needs is that"
" mostly, they'll tell you what they are! They'll do that right in the job"
" advertisement, for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:44
msgid ""
"Sometimes, it can also help to do a bit of :ref:`reading between the "
"lines <between-the-lines>` to get at what they need - but *always start "
"with what they say*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:46
msgid ""
"You might judge that one of the problems they have is poor testing "
"discipline in their engineering team - they need *someone to improve the "
"team's testing practices*, not just someone who writes good tests "
"themselves. Write that down, so that it's staring you in the face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:48
msgid ""
"**What value do you have that can meet their needs?** Now think about "
"yourself, and what you have that connects to those needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:50
msgid ""
"You might have many good qualities, but you need to identify the ones "
"that will matter to them; write those down too. Perhaps you think: *I am "
"pretty good at getting people to do new things*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:52
msgid ""
"**How can you demonstrate that you'll be able to bring that value?** The "
"key word here is *demonstrate*. For example, perhaps in a previous role, "
"you got the whole office to embrace recycling, despite initial skepticism"
" from management and resistance from some colleagues - that shows your "
"ability to bring people along with you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:54
msgid ""
"It's useless to *tell* them \"I'll be very successful at changing a "
"team's attitude towards testing\". You have to *show* them something."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:58
msgid ""
"This uses two essential interview techniques you need to get used to "
"using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:60
msgid ":ref:`using stories <vurt:interviewing-rules-tell-stories>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:61
msgid ":ref:`demonstrating value <vurt:interviewing-rules-demonstrate-value>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:63
msgid "Here's another example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:65
msgid ""
"One of the things you read is that they want to establish *more rigorous "
"platform operating procedures* (**need**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:66
msgid ""
"You can help meet that need, because you *enjoy creating documentation, "
"and you are good at it* (**value**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:67
msgid ""
"What could show that? Your story of *how you wrote up the post-mortem "
"following a security incident, and used it to create the standard "
"security incident operating procedure* (**demonstration**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:71
msgid ""
"And that way you can end up with something like the table below, a tool "
"to have at your fingertips when you need it - especially valuable to have"
" as an aide-memoire in an interview situation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:78
msgid "their needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:79
msgid "value I can bring"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:80
msgid "demonstration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:81
msgid "someone to improve the team's testing practices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:82
msgid "I am pretty good at getting people to do new things"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:83
msgid "how I got the whole office to embrace recycling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:84
msgid "more rigorous platform operating procedures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:85
msgid "I enjoy creating documentation, and I am good at it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../interview-success-performance.rst:86
msgid ""
"how I wrote up the post-mortem following a security incident, and used it"
" to create what is now our standard operating procedure for responding to"
" security incidents"
msgstr ""

